question: Jason and Ava have 72 minutes to walk to the bank together. It takes them 29 minutes to get to the corner where the school is. It takes them another 32 minutes to get to the library. How much longer do they have to get to bank without being late?
answer:
Jason and Ava arrive at the school with 72 - 29 = <<72-29=43>>43 minutes left to reach the library.
They then arrive at the library and have 43 - 32 = <<43-32=11>>11 minutes left to get to bank without being late.
#### 11
